Interface Event4Delegate<T1,T2,T3,T4>

  • Type Parameters:
    T1 - The type of the first information parameter the event provides
    T2 - The type of the second information parameter the event provides
    T3 - The type of the third information parameter the event provides
    T4 - The type of the fourth information parameter the event provides
    All Superinterfaces:
    Action4<T1,T2,T3,T4>, Event4<T1,T2,T3,T4>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Event4AsyncDelegate<T1,T2,T3,T4>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Event4AsyncAdapter, Event4Caller, Event4Distributor

    public interface Event4Delegate<T1,T2,T3,T4>
extends Action4<T1,T2,T3,T4>, Event4<T1,T2,T3,T4>
    An Event4Delegate implements Action4 as well as Event4 and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action4 interface to all subscribers of the Event4 interface.
    Author:
    tilmann
